  <h1>Possessive Adjectives and Pronouns Practice</h1>

  <div class="container">
    <p><strong>Instructions:</strong> Fill in the blank with the correct possessive adjective or possessive pronoun from the choices provided.</p>

    <div class="meta">
      <div>Name: _________________________</div>
      <div>Date: _________________________</div>
    </div>

    <div class="question">1. She keeps <input type="text" /> <span class="choices">(her / hers)</span> work space very clean.</div>
    <div class="question">2. She never eats at <input type="text" /> <span class="choices">(her / hers)</span> desk, but they always eat at <input type="text" /> <span class="choices">(their / theirs)</span>.</div>
    <div class="question">3. That office is <input type="text" /> <span class="choices">(you / yours)</span>.</div>
    <div class="question">4. <input type="text" /> <span class="choices">(Theirs / Their)</span> company has more employees than his.</div>
    <div class="question">5. That's <input type="text" /> <span class="choices">(your / yours)</span> book. Where is <input type="text" /> <span class="choices">(my / mine)</span>?</div>
    <div class="question">6. We will give you <input type="text" /> <span class="choices">(our / ours)</span> plan so you can compare it with <input type="text" /> <span class="choices">(your / yours)</span>.</div>
    <div class="question">7. The dog loves <input type="text" /> <span class="choices">(its / it's)</span> new toy.</div>
    <div class="question">8. Is this car <input type="text" /> <span class="choices">(your / yours)</span> or <input type="text" /> <span class="choices">(our / ours)</span>?</div>
    <div class="question">9. <input type="text" /> <span class="choices">(His / Him)</span> report was more detailed than <input type="text" /> <span class="choices">(my / mine)</span>.</div>
    <div class="question">10. They brought <input type="text" /> <span class="choices">(their / theirs)</span> own lunches, but we forgot <input type="text" /> <span class="choices">(our / ours)</span>.</div>
    <div class="question">11. I think this jacket is <input type="text" /> <span class="choices">(her / hers)</span>.</div>
    <div class="question">12. <input type="text" /> <span class="choices">(Whose / Who's)</span> pen is this? Is it <input type="text" /> <span class="choices">(your / yours)</span>?</div>
    <div class="question">13. The cat chased <input type="text" /> <span class="choices">(its / it's)</span> tail.</div>
    <div class="question">14. <input type="text" /> <span class="choices">(Our / Ours)</span> team played better than <input type="text" /> <span class="choices">(their / theirs)</span>.</div>
    <div class="question">15. He shared <input type="text" /> <span class="choices">(his / him)</span> ideas, and I shared <input type="text" /> <span class="choices">(my / mine)</span>.</div>
    <div class="question">16. The house lost <input type="text" /> <span class="choices">(its / it's)</span> roof in the storm.</div>
    <div class="question">17. Don't touch that; it's <input type="text" /> <span class="choices">(my / mine)</span>!</div>
    <div class="question">18. They finished <input type="text" /> <span class="choices">(their / theirs)</span> work early.</div>
    <div class="question">19. This laptop is <input type="text" /> <span class="choices">(my / mine)</span>, but that one is <input type="text" /> <span class="choices">(her / hers)</span>.</div>
    <div class="question">20. Do you know if this phone is <input type="text" /> <span class="choices">(her / hers)</span>?</div>

